## Handoff

### Gate 3: Plan review

```bash
# 1. Commit the plan
git add {{.RigRoot}}/docs/plans/<bead-id>.md
git commit -m "plan: project plan for <bead-id> - <brief description>"
git push

# 2. Update bead
bd update <bead-id> --status needs-review

# 3. Mail + nudge crew
CREW_AGENT="<agent-id of crew member who assigned you>"
gc mail send $CREW_AGENT -s "Project plan ready for review: <bead-id>" -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Project plan is ready at {{.RigRoot}}/docs/plans/<bead-id>.md

Phases: <N>
Total tasks: <N> (<N> automated, <N> manual/human-required)

Manual steps requiring your attention before work can proceed:
- Phase 1: <manual step 1>
- Phase 2: <manual step 2>

Please review and reply with approval or feedback.
EOF
)"
gc nudge $CREW_AGENT "Project plan ready for review: <bead-id>"
```

**Then stop.** Do not create beads until crew explicitly approves the plan.

### Gate 3 approval: bead backlog creation

When crew approves (they will mail you and reassign the bead):

```bash
# Create all child beads per the Bead Creation Plan section above
# Then mail + nudge crew with summary

gc mail send $CREW_AGENT -s "Bead backlog created: <bead-id>" -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Created <N> child beads from the approved plan.

Manual steps (needs-human) — action these first:
- <bead-id-1>: <description>
- <bead-id-2>: <description>

Automated tasks ready for dispatch:
- <N> tasks labeled pool:{{.Rig}}/polecat, waiting for manual steps to clear

View full backlog: bd list --parent <bead-id>
EOF
)"
gc nudge $CREW_AGENT "Bead backlog ready: bd list --parent <bead-id>"
```

